<H1>Rebecca J. Passonneau</H1> 
<BLOCKQUOTE><P><I>To work is to live without dying.</I>
<B>Rainer Maria Rilke</B></P></BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR> 
<P>Rebecca Passonneau (Ph.D. in Linguistics, University of Chicago, 
1985) works concurrently as a 
Research Scientist in the 
<!WA0><A HREF="http://www.cs.columbia.edu/">
   <B>Department of Computer Science</B></A>
at 
<!WA1><A HREF="http://www.cc.columbia.edu/">
   <B>Columbia University</B></A>
and as a Visiting Research Scientist
in <!WA2><A HREF="http://www.bellcore.com/tech_int.html">
Bellcore's Applied Research Group</A>. 
Previously she worked in the Natural Language Group,
Paoli Research Center, Unisys.
</P> 
<HR> 
